# Python Virtual Environment Only

All Python work in this project MUST use a project-local virtual environment. Never install packages globally.

## Rules

- Always create and use `.venv` in the project root
- Never run `pip install` outside an activated venv
- Never use `pip install --user` or global pip installs
- Re-activate the venv before any `python`, `pip`, or `streamlit` command

## Setup

```bash
cd ~/workspace/"NYU Cloud and API Automation Developer Application Sample App"
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Running the app

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate
streamlit run app.py
```

## Examples

```bash
# BAD — global install
pip install streamlit

# GOOD — venv install
source .venv/bin/activate && pip install streamlit
```
